Package org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.interfaces

Interface Value

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DatatypeIdValue, EntityIdValue, GlobeCoordinatesValue, IriIdentifiedValue, ItemIdValue, MonolingualTextValue, PropertyIdValue, QuantityValue, StringValue, TimeValue
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DatatypeIdImpl, GlobeCoordinatesValueImpl, ItemIdValueImpl, JacksonDatatypeId, JacksonMonolingualTextValue, JacksonValue, JacksonValueEntityId, JacksonValueGlobeCoordinates, JacksonValueItemId, JacksonValueMonolingualText, JacksonValuePropertyId, JacksonValueQuantity, JacksonValueString, JacksonValueTime, MonolingualTextValueImpl, PropertyIdValueImpl, QuantityValueImpl, StringValueImpl, TimeValueImpl

    public interface Value
    A Value is the most general kind of object in the Wikibase datamodel. It can represent anything that can be the value of a user-defined property or of a system property that is not represented to the user (e.g., the datatype or list of aliases might be represented as a value, even though there is no user property with values of this type).
    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch
